## Markdown in R

### A Few Examples with plain text

#### 1. italics **I *can* complete the midterm**

#### 2. strikethrough: I ~~can~~ complete the midterm

#### 3. hiding my code with echo=False:


::: {.cell}
::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
[1] "I can complete the midterm"
```
:::
:::


#### 4. showing code:


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
print("I can complete the midterm")
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
[1] "I can complete the midterm"
```
:::
:::


### Some Math

#### 1. simple addition


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
5 + 5
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
[1] 10
```
:::
:::


### 2. square root


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
sqrt(100)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
[1] 10
```
:::
:::


#### 3. sum of a range of numbers


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
sum(1:4)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
[1] 10
```
:::
:::
